<body>
    <table style="width:900px;border-width: 0">
        <tr>
            <td style="width:140px;height: 20px;vertical-align: top">&nbsp;</td>
            <td align="center" valign="top"></td>
            <td style="width:140px;height: 20px;text-align: right;vertical-align: top" class="normal_body">
                @DateTime.Today.ToLongDateString()
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    <div class="main_header_section">Line fill rate & average lead time KPI</div>
    <div>The attached reports show the following:</div>
    <br />
    <div style="font-weight:bold;">Line Fill Rate</div>

    <div>
        Shows the requested order lines shipped complete as a percentage of all requested order lines.
    </div>

    <div style="font-style:italic;">
        Example: A client orders 100 lines, when the order is shipped 95 of those lines are shipped complete (as per the original order quantity).<br />
        This means the line fill rate for that order is 95%
    </div>
    <br />
    <div>
        The average line fill rate over the last 6 months was @lineFillSixMonths.ToString("P1")
    </div>
    <div>
        The average line fill rate for @DateTime.Now.AddMonths(-1).ToString("MMMM yyyy") was @lineFillCurrentMonth.ToString("P1")
    </div>
    <div>
        Over the next 6 months we will be working towards achieving a target line fill rate of 98.0%
    </div>
    <br />

    <div style="font-weight:bold;">Average actual lead time</div>
    <div>
        Based on the original order date we plot the number of days for each order between order date and actual shipment date.<br />
        We show on the chart all orders that have been created in the last 6 months that have been shipped.<br />
        The trend line shows therefore the average actual lead time.<br />
    </div>
    <div>
        Shipping depends on the loading location and destination port and is approximately 4-6 weeks.
    </div>
    <br />
    <div>
        The average actual lead time over the last 6 months was @averageLeadTimeValue.ToString("N1") days.
    </div>
    <div>
        Over the next 6 months we will be working towards achieving an average of 35 days
    </div>
</body>
